1
00:00:01,106 --> 00:00:03,442
[♪ pop music playing]

2
00:00:45,359 --> 00:00:49,071
PERFECT CROWN

3
00:00:59,956 --> 00:01:01,083
THIS IS A WORK OF FICTION

4
00:01:01,166 --> 00:01:03,085
CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
WERE FILMED SAFELY

5
00:01:04,753 --> 00:01:06,755
[♪ ethereal music playing]

6
00:01:16,723 --> 00:01:18,684
[officiant] All rise
for His Majesty the King!

7
00:02:06,356 --> 00:02:08,483
Let us begin the discussion on abolishing…

8
00:02:10,360 --> 00:02:11,361
the monarchy.

9
00:02:13,238 --> 00:02:16,032
[♪ inspiring music playing]

10
00:02:22,289 --> 00:02:25,584
PERFECT CROWN

11
00:02:33,592 --> 00:02:35,051
So… No, no.

12
00:02:38,096 --> 00:02:39,181
[sighs]

13
00:02:45,103 --> 00:02:47,397
He should have told them by now, right?

14
00:02:47,481 --> 00:02:48,482
Yes, he should have.

15
00:02:48,565 --> 00:02:51,526
[gasps] The court historians
must've recorded it by now, right?

16
00:02:51,610 --> 00:02:53,945
Once it's in the records,
it's set in stone.

17
00:02:54,029 --> 00:02:55,155
We're in trouble now.

18
00:02:55,238 --> 00:02:57,866
This won't do. I'll call Hyejeong…
I mean, Aide Do--

19
00:02:57,949 --> 00:02:58,950
Just shush!

20
00:03:06,374 --> 00:03:09,503
Tomorrow, you'll be His Majesty,
and not His Royal Highness.

21
00:03:11,046 --> 00:03:12,589
You'll also be Queen tomorrow,

22
00:03:12,672 --> 00:03:13,882
and not the Grand Princess.

23
00:03:15,926 --> 00:03:17,719
What will you record first in the Annals?

24
00:03:21,431 --> 00:03:24,309
On the day the newly crowned king
first enters the Throne Hall,

25
00:03:24,392 --> 00:03:27,562
all are assembled,
from the Cabinet to the royal family.

26
00:03:28,271 --> 00:03:30,607
Like a traditional ceremony of sorts?

27
00:03:31,525 --> 00:03:33,193
With all the court historians too.

28
00:03:34,152 --> 00:03:35,153
Yeah.

29
00:03:35,237 --> 00:03:37,572
I didn't even know this was a big deal.

30
00:03:38,198 --> 00:03:39,533
I've seen so many gatherings.

31
00:03:39,616 --> 00:03:40,617
[chuckles]

32
00:03:42,077 --> 00:03:44,746
That's because we caused them
a great deal of trouble.

33
00:03:48,792 --> 00:03:49,793
So?

34
00:03:50,877 --> 00:03:52,963
What will be
your first proclamation as King?
STYLE
::cue()

35
00:04:04,349 --> 00:04:05,934
-[♪ soft music playing]
-Words that…

36
00:04:09,688 --> 00:04:10,939
carry great weight.

37
00:04:15,694 --> 00:04:17,153
The backlash could be severe.

38
00:04:19,739 --> 00:04:21,157
But still, I'm sure you…

39
00:04:22,242 --> 00:04:23,577
I will understand you.

40
00:04:33,086 --> 00:04:34,462
I'm going to abolish the Crown.

41
00:04:35,130 --> 00:04:37,257
[♪ music builds]

42
00:04:38,633 --> 00:04:39,843
Inherited titles and status

43
00:04:40,510 --> 00:04:42,053
can become a privilege

44
00:04:43,054 --> 00:04:44,055
or a constraint.

45
00:04:46,933 --> 00:04:48,184
It all stems from the Crown.

46
00:04:55,984 --> 00:04:57,652
I thought it was treason.

47
00:05:01,239 --> 00:05:02,574
Turns out it was a revolution.

48
00:05:03,992 --> 00:05:04,993
Your dream.

49
00:05:18,673 --> 00:05:20,091
You've just attained this title.

50
00:05:20,926 --> 00:05:22,594
Are you ready to let it go?

51
00:05:22,677 --> 00:05:26,514
[chuckles] I never said I wanted status.

52
00:05:27,974 --> 00:05:30,435
I was just pissed off
about the opportunities it cost me.

53
00:05:36,149 --> 00:05:37,359
That's when I knew.

54
00:05:39,152 --> 00:05:40,153
That you'd be…

55
00:05:41,696 --> 00:05:42,697
my revolution.

56
00:05:44,282 --> 00:05:46,284
[♪ powerful music playing]

57
00:06:01,716 --> 00:06:02,884
[aide] Your Majesty.

58
00:06:03,468 --> 00:06:04,844
Abolition of the monarchy?

59
00:06:04,928 --> 00:06:06,471
You cannot mean what you say.

60
00:06:06,972 --> 00:06:09,683
Every year, most nations
with constitutional monarchies

61
00:06:09,766 --> 00:06:11,810
revisit the question
of their own abolition.

62
00:06:11,893 --> 00:06:13,728
But that is…

63
00:06:13,812 --> 00:06:15,271
Prime Minister Min.

64
00:06:15,981 --> 00:06:16,982
Yes, Your Majesty.

65
00:06:17,065 --> 00:06:18,900
What about our country?

66
00:06:19,484 --> 00:06:23,279
We conduct formal opinion polls,
but opposition remains high every year.

67
00:06:23,363 --> 00:06:25,365
I believe the divide is not so vast.

68
00:06:27,075 --> 00:06:28,451
For a decade now,

69
00:06:29,202 --> 00:06:30,870
that gap has steadily narrowed.

70
00:06:30,954 --> 00:06:33,707
The Crown does not exist
to prove its worth.

71
00:06:35,792 --> 00:06:38,420
Its value lies in its very existence.

72
00:06:41,214 --> 00:06:42,716
[laughing]

73
00:06:46,428 --> 00:06:49,389
"We do not need a king
who lacks the people's support."

74
00:06:50,515 --> 00:06:51,933
I believe those were your words.

75
00:06:54,936 --> 00:06:55,937
Have you forgotten?

76
00:06:56,563 --> 00:06:58,565
[♪ tense music playing]

77
00:07:08,992 --> 00:07:10,452
Kings may come and go…

78
00:07:16,291 --> 00:07:17,792
but the Crown endures.

79
00:07:24,132 --> 00:07:26,217
[Huiju] You're saying the Cabinet
and Royal Relatives

80
00:07:26,301 --> 00:07:28,178
will oppose it, no question?

81
00:07:28,803 --> 00:07:29,971
Yes.

82
00:07:30,054 --> 00:07:33,433
Most of the establishment
is connected to the Crown.

83
00:07:33,516 --> 00:07:36,603
The monarchy and the political world
have always sustained each other.

84
00:07:36,686 --> 00:07:38,772
The Royal Relatives go without saying.

85
00:07:40,982 --> 00:07:42,734
So His Majesty has nothing to rely on

86
00:07:43,943 --> 00:07:45,487
but public sentiment.
STYLE
::cue()

87
00:07:50,116 --> 00:07:51,493
-There he is!
-He's here!

88
00:07:51,576 --> 00:07:53,244
[journalists clamoring]

89
00:07:55,038 --> 00:07:57,207
Is it true there are talks
of abolishing the monarchy?

90
00:07:57,290 --> 00:07:59,000
Is this your first time hearing about it?

91
00:08:04,380 --> 00:08:05,965
The people of this nation

92
00:08:06,049 --> 00:08:08,301
have nothing to worry about.

93
00:08:09,302 --> 00:08:11,137
Please say more!

94
00:08:11,221 --> 00:08:12,639
One more statement, please!

95
00:08:12,722 --> 00:08:14,724
[clamoring continues]

96
00:08:16,392 --> 00:08:19,312
The release
of the 34th monarch's first agenda

97
00:08:19,395 --> 00:08:21,481
has triggered a major stir.

98
00:08:21,564 --> 00:08:25,068
This agenda starts the discussion
on the abolition of the monarchy.

99
00:08:25,151 --> 00:08:27,487
As Prime Minister Min left the palace,

100
00:08:27,570 --> 00:08:29,113
he reassured the public…

101
00:08:29,197 --> 00:08:30,573
He just ascended the throne.

102
00:08:30,657 --> 00:08:32,575
Why would he abolish the monarchy?

103
00:08:32,659 --> 00:08:33,660
I know, right?

104
00:08:33,743 --> 00:08:35,954
Do you think Father knows about this?

105
00:08:36,579 --> 00:08:37,956
Damn it…

106
00:08:39,332 --> 00:08:40,542
[both sigh]

107
00:08:46,714 --> 00:08:47,715
[door opens]

108
00:09:17,453 --> 00:09:20,039
How dare you show your face here?

109
00:09:22,959 --> 00:09:24,711
I wanted to see for myself

110
00:09:26,004 --> 00:09:27,797
the gravity of the sins I have committed.

111
00:09:27,881 --> 00:09:30,800
Do you even realize what you have done?

112
00:09:32,177 --> 00:09:35,138
I'm asking if it feels good
to cast aside your own father and son.

113
00:09:37,223 --> 00:09:39,517
Have you no pity for that poor boy,

114
00:09:40,894 --> 00:09:44,564
now cast into the shadows
like some relic of a bygone age?

115
00:09:46,983 --> 00:09:48,109
That poor boy…

116
00:09:51,154 --> 00:09:52,530
knew everything all along.

117
00:09:55,158 --> 00:09:57,327
He knew the full measure of my sins,

118
00:09:59,037 --> 00:10:01,539
and he silently shouldered
that heavy burden.

119
00:10:02,123 --> 00:10:03,208
What are you saying?

120
00:10:03,291 --> 00:10:05,126
Do you know how I felt

121
00:10:06,294 --> 00:10:08,796
when I learned of your sins?

122
00:10:12,842 --> 00:10:14,719
When you so proudly claimed

123
00:10:16,012 --> 00:10:17,555
that it was all for my sake.

124
00:10:19,807 --> 00:10:23,019
Do you know how that made me feel?

125
00:10:30,193 --> 00:10:31,194
So…

126
00:10:33,238 --> 00:10:35,240
may this mark the end of your sins.

127
00:10:36,991 --> 00:10:38,159
From this day forth…

128
00:10:42,163 --> 00:10:43,581
you have no daughter to claim.

129
00:10:53,049 --> 00:10:55,051
[♪ somber music playing]

130
00:10:57,762 --> 00:10:58,805
Your Majesty!

131
00:11:02,100 --> 00:11:03,726
Prime Minister Min, that bastard…

132
00:11:14,988 --> 00:11:16,823
He knew about the explosion

133
00:11:17,824 --> 00:11:20,576
when he drew
the Grand Prince to that place.

134
00:11:23,079 --> 00:11:25,707
You must stop either
the Grand Prince or His Majesty.

135
00:11:27,041 --> 00:11:28,209
Do whatever you must.

136
00:11:40,722 --> 00:11:42,849
[♪ menacing music playing]

137
00:12:09,042 --> 00:12:10,043
Let me escort you

138
00:12:11,044 --> 00:12:12,628
back to the palace.

139
00:12:19,302 --> 00:12:20,636
[phone buzzing]

140
00:12:22,180 --> 00:12:25,099
MY SON
STYLE
::cue()

141
00:12:35,485 --> 00:12:36,486
[Taeju] There he is.

142
00:12:36,569 --> 00:12:37,570
Father.

143
00:12:37,653 --> 00:12:40,907
Is it true what they're saying
about abolishing the monarchy?

144
00:12:40,990 --> 00:12:42,325
-They're not, right?
-Are they?

145
00:12:42,408 --> 00:12:44,118
How can they abolish the Crown?

146
00:12:44,202 --> 00:12:45,995
Father, say something.

147
00:12:48,623 --> 00:12:50,958
[sighs] My brother-in-law just
became King.

148
00:12:51,042 --> 00:12:53,252
How can they abolish it already?

149
00:12:53,336 --> 00:12:55,088
-"Brother-in-law"?
-Why? What's wrong?

150
00:12:55,171 --> 00:12:56,923
He is my brother-in-law, right?

151
00:12:57,006 --> 00:12:58,508
Address him properly.

152
00:12:59,050 --> 00:13:00,927
You don't want to get people talking.

153
00:13:01,010 --> 00:13:02,303
Let's not kid ourselves.

154
00:13:02,387 --> 00:13:04,514
There's no title to speak of
if there's no Crown.

155
00:13:04,597 --> 00:13:06,891
You just became Lord JUNGHWA.
You're finally a lord--

156
00:13:06,974 --> 00:13:08,059
Taeju!

157
00:13:13,815 --> 00:13:15,608
For the time being,

158
00:13:17,026 --> 00:13:18,111
watch your backs.

159
00:13:20,154 --> 00:13:21,155
Our backs?

160
00:13:21,239 --> 00:13:24,158
Why would you say
something like that, Father?

161
00:13:24,242 --> 00:13:25,284
You're scaring me.

162
00:13:29,288 --> 00:13:30,289
Wait…

163
00:13:36,879 --> 00:13:39,924
There will be another discussion
on the monarchy's abolition next week.

164
00:13:40,800 --> 00:13:43,511
His Majesty will seek to leave
that decision to the people.

165
00:13:44,303 --> 00:13:45,555
The Cabinet will oppose it.

166
00:13:46,639 --> 00:13:49,559
I'll need you
to voice your objection there.

167
00:13:55,565 --> 00:13:57,275
I am powerless.

168
00:13:59,861 --> 00:14:01,487
I'm not asking you to exercise power.

169
00:14:02,280 --> 00:14:04,282
Simply hint that the abolition
of the monarchy

170
00:14:04,365 --> 00:14:08,202
is His Majesty's own pursuit,
not the will of the Crown.

171
00:14:08,953 --> 00:14:10,037
And if I refuse?

172
00:14:11,539 --> 00:14:13,249
What will happen then?

173
00:14:18,796 --> 00:14:21,716
Do you wish to see your only son
follow in your father's footsteps…

174
00:14:24,427 --> 00:14:25,928
and be branded a criminal as well?

175
00:14:39,692 --> 00:14:40,902
[Hyejeong] Your Majesty.

176
00:14:42,653 --> 00:14:44,363
Prime Minister Min is not holding back.

177
00:14:44,447 --> 00:14:46,532
The palace budget has been put on hold.

178
00:14:52,413 --> 00:14:55,499
I knew he'd try to rein us in,
but I expected a different approach.

179
00:14:55,583 --> 00:14:57,543
Snipping the purse strings was a low blow.

180
00:14:57,627 --> 00:14:59,712
This will immobilize
the Queen's Quarters first.

181
00:14:59,795 --> 00:15:02,131
The royal finances are
under the Queen's jurisdiction.

182
00:15:02,757 --> 00:15:05,551
She just became Queen
and is already set to come under fire.

183
00:15:06,052 --> 00:15:07,428
What's the most pressing issue?

184
00:15:08,012 --> 00:15:09,430
The palace attendants' salaries.

185
00:15:09,972 --> 00:15:11,974
The Royal Guard
and administrative officials…

186
00:15:13,059 --> 00:15:14,060
[Huiju chortles]
STYLE
::cue()

187
00:15:14,769 --> 00:15:15,770
Excuse me.

188
00:15:16,896 --> 00:15:18,064
I'm Seong Huiju.

189
00:15:18,689 --> 00:15:20,358
The only money problems I've had were,

190
00:15:20,441 --> 00:15:22,985
"Gosh, how am I ever going
to spend all this money?"

191
00:15:23,069 --> 00:15:24,320
That's it.

192
00:15:24,403 --> 00:15:26,405
So what? Will you donate to the Crown?

193
00:15:26,489 --> 00:15:27,907
Yeah.

194
00:15:27,990 --> 00:15:29,242
-What?
-[sighs]

195
00:15:29,951 --> 00:15:33,246
What's the point of having wealthy in-laws
if you can't make use of them?

196
00:15:33,329 --> 00:15:36,082
-Let me see. How short is the budget?
-Well, this is…

197
00:15:36,165 --> 00:15:38,626
I appreciate the sentiment, but no.

198
00:15:39,126 --> 00:15:40,753
We need to think long-term.

199
00:15:40,836 --> 00:15:43,214
We can't think long-term right now.

200
00:15:43,297 --> 00:15:44,840
I already told you.

201
00:15:45,341 --> 00:15:47,385
When you pursue
a venture everyone opposes,

202
00:15:47,468 --> 00:15:49,804
you can't give them the time to object.

203
00:15:54,517 --> 00:15:56,352
PRIME MINISTER MIN JEONGWOO

204
00:15:56,978 --> 00:15:59,897
The Crown must've been up in arms.
Thank you for handling that.

205
00:15:59,981 --> 00:16:01,274
Actually, sir…

206
00:16:07,113 --> 00:16:10,241
The palace turned down funding
for the second half of the year.

207
00:16:12,535 --> 00:16:14,453
But they won't
be able to operate without it.

208
00:16:14,537 --> 00:16:16,872
Castle Group has made
a donation to the Crown.

209
00:16:16,956 --> 00:16:19,709
The amount they received
exceeds their annual budget.

210
00:16:21,419 --> 00:16:23,421
[sighs]

211
00:16:27,133 --> 00:16:29,093
Look at His Majesty
making use of his in-laws.

212
00:16:30,469 --> 00:16:31,470
How petty.

213
00:16:34,849 --> 00:16:35,850
[sighs]

214
00:16:36,600 --> 00:16:38,519
GREMLIN

215
00:16:38,602 --> 00:16:40,104
[phone buzzing]

216
00:16:45,776 --> 00:16:46,861
Hey, Dayeong.

217
00:16:46,944 --> 00:16:48,404
I'm a bit busy right now.

218
00:16:58,497 --> 00:17:00,708
What's going on? What summons?

219
00:17:02,501 --> 00:17:04,003
Is this intel from your family?

220
00:17:04,920 --> 00:17:05,921
Yes.

221
00:17:06,005 --> 00:17:07,798
It's a slush fund probe.

222
00:17:07,882 --> 00:17:11,218
They say a formal summons
will be issued within a day or two…

223
00:17:14,722 --> 00:17:15,723
This is clearly

224
00:17:16,974 --> 00:17:18,392
a direct attack on me.

225
00:17:18,476 --> 00:17:20,353
If you know that, don't play into it.

226
00:17:20,436 --> 00:17:21,437
I won't.

227
00:17:22,480 --> 00:17:24,607
It's a threat to deter us
from funding the Crown.

228
00:17:26,067 --> 00:17:27,943
Why give them the satisfaction?

229
00:17:32,239 --> 00:17:33,324
What's with that face?

230
00:17:34,408 --> 00:17:35,409
[Huiju] Dayeong.

231
00:17:35,493 --> 00:17:37,745
Can you check
who is leading the investigation?

232
00:17:37,828 --> 00:17:39,288
Why do you ask?

233
00:17:40,039 --> 00:17:41,582
I'm going to change the narrative.

234
00:17:42,166 --> 00:17:43,209
From slush funds

235
00:17:44,377 --> 00:17:45,544
to abuse of power.

236
00:17:51,509 --> 00:17:52,677
Well, in that case…

237
00:17:53,344 --> 00:17:54,887
I'll go in for questioning, Father.

238
00:17:55,429 --> 00:17:58,224
Are you nuts? Why would you do that?

239
00:17:58,307 --> 00:18:00,518
Father's blood pressure
has been acting up and all.

240
00:18:00,601 --> 00:18:03,604
The stress from all the questioning
might just push him over the edge.

241
00:18:03,688 --> 00:18:08,526
And it's only right for the successor
to handle these matters.

242
00:18:09,193 --> 00:18:11,570
-Babe, are you still drunk?
-Don't be absurd--

243
00:18:11,654 --> 00:18:13,280
Go ahead then.

244
00:18:14,281 --> 00:18:15,658
What?

245
00:18:17,159 --> 00:18:20,371
A bit of media exposure
wouldn't be the worst thing.

246
00:18:20,454 --> 00:18:21,872
Father.

247
00:18:22,540 --> 00:18:23,582
Is that all, Father?

248
00:18:23,666 --> 00:18:26,877
I've actually been meaning
to say this for a while now.

249
00:18:26,961 --> 00:18:30,005
Right now, I'm offering
to take your place in the investigation,

250
00:18:30,089 --> 00:18:31,340
out of pure filial devotion.

251
00:18:31,424 --> 00:18:34,343
I'm not asking
for tears of gratitude, am I?

252
00:18:34,427 --> 00:18:35,678
But maybe a little praise?

253
00:18:35,761 --> 00:18:37,096
Or at least a warm…

254
00:18:37,972 --> 00:18:39,014
What? Too far?

255
00:18:40,725 --> 00:18:41,726
I'm off.

256
00:18:41,809 --> 00:18:42,810
[Hyeonguk] Wait.

257
00:18:43,769 --> 00:18:46,105
Don't just sit there.
Escort her back to the palace.

258
00:18:46,689 --> 00:18:47,982
Me? Escort who?

259
00:18:48,733 --> 00:18:49,734
Her?

260
00:18:56,824 --> 00:18:58,200
You shouldn't be out alone.

261
00:19:14,300 --> 00:19:15,509
What? What now?

262
00:19:16,093 --> 00:19:19,305
Castle Beauty's legal team
is highly capable.

263
00:19:19,388 --> 00:19:20,723
What?

264
00:19:21,849 --> 00:19:23,184
Let me know if you need help.

265
00:19:27,646 --> 00:19:28,647
You worried about me?

266
00:19:28,731 --> 00:19:30,441
[scoffs] You must be insane.

267
00:19:31,734 --> 00:19:33,152
That's not it.

268
00:19:33,235 --> 00:19:34,945
You're going in Father's place.

269
00:19:35,446 --> 00:19:36,655
So do it right.

270
00:19:37,364 --> 00:19:38,741
Don't give them any ammunition.

271
00:19:40,910 --> 00:19:43,496
Hey, I have years of experience
as a wealthy heir too.

272
00:19:44,497 --> 00:19:46,165
You're the only one who belittles me.

273
00:19:46,248 --> 00:19:47,291
Just you.

274
00:19:49,543 --> 00:19:50,961
I'll try to be less harsh now.

275
00:19:52,046 --> 00:19:53,255
Brother.

276
00:19:55,591 --> 00:19:56,592
"Brother"?

277
00:19:59,553 --> 00:20:01,722
Wait, what are you going to do?

278
00:20:02,473 --> 00:20:03,474
What was it? [chuckles]

279
00:20:03,557 --> 00:20:04,558
You're doing what now?

280
00:20:04,642 --> 00:20:06,602
[♪ tender music playing]
STYLE
::cue()

281
00:20:11,816 --> 00:20:14,193
"I'll try to be less harsh now."

282
00:20:15,110 --> 00:20:18,239
[laughs] No way.

283
00:20:20,783 --> 00:20:23,744
[Lady Choi] Your Majesty,
the Queen has arrived.

284
00:20:24,245 --> 00:20:25,704
-Show her in.
-[door slides open]

285
00:20:28,165 --> 00:20:29,291
[chuckles]

286
00:20:30,084 --> 00:20:31,961
[Huiju groaning]

287
00:20:33,170 --> 00:20:34,213
What's wrong?

288
00:20:34,797 --> 00:20:36,382
I'm exhausted.

289
00:20:45,474 --> 00:20:47,184
I went to see Father today.

290
00:20:49,103 --> 00:20:50,104
Your father?

291
00:20:50,938 --> 00:20:51,981
Nobody told me that.

292
00:20:52,565 --> 00:20:54,525
I slipped out alone
without telling anyone,

293
00:20:54,608 --> 00:20:56,360
so don't give Aide Choi a hard time.

294
00:20:58,654 --> 00:20:59,655
You went alone?

295
00:21:00,281 --> 00:21:01,699
I had no other choice.

296
00:21:02,533 --> 00:21:03,826
I was feeling too restless.

297
00:21:05,995 --> 00:21:07,037
Why?

298
00:21:14,587 --> 00:21:15,838
As early as tomorrow,

299
00:21:16,630 --> 00:21:18,799
prosecutors will begin
investigating Castle Group.

300
00:21:22,094 --> 00:21:23,387
-Hold on. Get up--
-[grunts]

301
00:21:26,849 --> 00:21:29,101
Father told me
not to play into their hands.

302
00:21:30,728 --> 00:21:34,982
Seong Taeju volunteered for questioning
with his chest all puffed up.

303
00:21:36,567 --> 00:21:37,985
It was so annoying.

304
00:21:38,068 --> 00:21:39,069
[clicks tongue]

305
00:21:39,153 --> 00:21:41,196
Why couldn't they just get angry?

306
00:21:41,280 --> 00:21:42,698
That would've been less awkward.

307
00:21:45,993 --> 00:21:46,994
Seong Huiju.

308
00:21:49,955 --> 00:21:51,707
Then again, you know…

309
00:21:52,291 --> 00:21:54,501
I mean, like… [chuckles]

310
00:21:56,086 --> 00:21:57,296
I didn't exactly hate it.

311
00:22:00,132 --> 00:22:01,759
It felt a bit reassuring,

312
00:22:02,551 --> 00:22:04,053
in a way.

313
00:22:10,768 --> 00:22:12,436
You should do that for me too.

314
00:22:13,938 --> 00:22:15,356
You should hold your ground

315
00:22:16,231 --> 00:22:17,441
and puff out your chest,

316
00:22:18,275 --> 00:22:19,443
so I can feel reassured.

317
00:22:19,526 --> 00:22:21,528
[♪ tender pop ballad playing]

318
00:22:32,873 --> 00:22:33,874
I will.

319
00:22:38,712 --> 00:22:39,713
Do it again.

320
00:22:42,299 --> 00:22:43,717
-Super reassuring, right?
-Yeah.

321
00:22:57,815 --> 00:23:00,776
[Jeongwoo] Do you wish to see your only
son follow in your father's footsteps…

322
00:23:02,403 --> 00:23:03,904
and be branded a criminal as well?

323
00:23:04,530 --> 00:23:06,490
[♪ dark music playing]

324
00:23:12,830 --> 00:23:14,331
What is that supposed to mean?

325
00:23:18,794 --> 00:23:20,546
I'm referring to three years ago,

326
00:23:20,629 --> 00:23:23,132
when you disposed
of the late King's royal edict.

327
00:23:30,889 --> 00:23:32,725
I do not know what you are talking about--

328
00:23:32,808 --> 00:23:36,103
If it's revealed you defied a royal decree
to seat your son upon the throne,

329
00:23:37,104 --> 00:23:38,188
the abdicated King

330
00:23:39,523 --> 00:23:41,608
will go down in history as a criminal.

331
00:23:44,361 --> 00:23:46,822
Not as a king or even a royal.

332
00:23:48,198 --> 00:23:49,283
Just a criminal.

333
00:23:52,703 --> 00:23:53,704
For eternity.

334
00:23:56,373 --> 00:23:57,750
How dare you…

335
00:24:02,504 --> 00:24:03,797
I've only kept my mouth shut

336
00:24:03,881 --> 00:24:06,091
because I was worried
the Crown would crumble.

337
00:24:08,886 --> 00:24:10,721
You worry that much about the Crown…

338
00:24:14,141 --> 00:24:15,934
yet you tried to kill I-AN?

339
00:24:26,528 --> 00:24:28,489
I am willing to do whatever it takes…

340
00:24:31,116 --> 00:24:32,659
as many times as necessary.

341
00:24:43,712 --> 00:24:45,130
[sighs]

342
00:24:48,759 --> 00:24:50,219
How difficult it is…

343
00:24:52,554 --> 00:24:54,014
just to keep you safe.
STYLE
::cue()

344
00:25:04,733 --> 00:25:06,151
[journalist] There he is!

345
00:25:06,235 --> 00:25:08,237
[muttering]

346
00:25:17,913 --> 00:25:19,581
Is it true that Castle Group maintains

347
00:25:19,665 --> 00:25:21,750
a slush fund
in the hundreds of billions of won?

348
00:25:21,834 --> 00:25:24,044
Can you explain the donation
you made to the Crown?

349
00:25:24,128 --> 00:25:26,505
Has the Queen reached out to you at all?

350
00:25:26,588 --> 00:25:28,132
Let's all calm down first.

351
00:25:28,215 --> 00:25:30,676
-Castle Group's slush fund…
-Let me just say this first.

352
00:25:31,844 --> 00:25:35,472
Well, you know, the Crown and the Cabinet

353
00:25:35,556 --> 00:25:38,225
just happens to be clashing
at this moment.

354
00:25:38,308 --> 00:25:40,644
The timing of this
seems just perfect, doesn't it?

355
00:25:40,727 --> 00:25:42,312
[sucks teeth] But still,

356
00:25:42,896 --> 00:25:45,399
I pledge to fully cooperate
with the investigation.

357
00:25:47,234 --> 00:25:48,485
[clamoring]

358
00:26:00,998 --> 00:26:02,291
Do you have something to say?

359
00:26:04,418 --> 00:26:05,419
No, Your Majesty.

360
00:26:10,382 --> 00:26:11,508
What is it?

361
00:26:12,176 --> 00:26:15,554
Perhaps you'd like
to visit the Queen Mother's Quarters?

362
00:26:18,348 --> 00:26:22,060
I believe you should if you want
to persuade the Office of Royal Relatives.

363
00:26:26,481 --> 00:26:27,649
Let her rest.

364
00:26:30,569 --> 00:26:32,529
She has only just ended her battle.

365
00:26:41,371 --> 00:26:42,831
Can you imagine it?

366
00:26:45,751 --> 00:26:47,878
This nation without a monarchy.

367
00:26:49,254 --> 00:26:50,881
I am curious.

368
00:26:55,219 --> 00:26:56,845
Are you not afraid?

369
00:26:56,929 --> 00:27:00,057
Are you afraid, Mother?

370
00:27:20,118 --> 00:27:21,245
[Hyeon] That's surprising.

371
00:27:22,454 --> 00:27:23,705
What is?

372
00:27:23,789 --> 00:27:26,667
I heard she's barely left
her quarters recently.

373
00:27:27,834 --> 00:27:28,835
Is that so?

374
00:27:29,378 --> 00:27:31,296
[Hyeon] After what happened
with Lord INPYEONG,

375
00:27:31,797 --> 00:27:34,841
she probably finds it difficult
to face the court attendants right now.

376
00:27:46,228 --> 00:27:48,230
Are you asking me for help?

377
00:27:49,856 --> 00:27:50,857
Yes.

378
00:27:52,651 --> 00:27:53,860
The royal family

379
00:27:55,278 --> 00:27:56,989
still listens to what you have to say.

380
00:27:59,282 --> 00:28:01,660
I had wondered why His Majesty
withheld his punishment.

381
00:28:04,371 --> 00:28:06,123
It appears he had his reasons.
STYLE
::cue()

382
00:28:29,271 --> 00:28:31,732
[line connects, rings]

383
00:28:32,607 --> 00:28:33,608
It is me.

384
00:28:40,532 --> 00:28:41,867
You made the right decision.

385
00:28:42,451 --> 00:28:44,453
[♪ menacing music playing]

386
00:29:31,416 --> 00:29:33,710
I have reviewed
the petition you have submitted.

387
00:29:36,546 --> 00:29:37,923
The royal family called upon me

388
00:29:38,006 --> 00:29:40,175
to safeguard the realm and the dynasty.

389
00:29:41,927 --> 00:29:44,554
And the Cabinet implored me
to fulfill my duties as the King.

390
00:29:45,639 --> 00:29:47,682
Is that correct?

391
00:29:48,892 --> 00:29:51,561
We were simply speaking
on behalf of the public, Your Majesty.

392
00:29:51,645 --> 00:29:52,687
Did you bother to ask?

393
00:29:54,022 --> 00:29:55,065
It is my understanding…

394
00:29:56,817 --> 00:29:58,527
that the people were never surveyed.

395
00:29:58,610 --> 00:30:00,112
[chuckles]

396
00:30:00,195 --> 00:30:01,196
Your Majesty.

397
00:30:01,822 --> 00:30:03,949
-The Cabinet was chosen by the people--
-So?

398
00:30:04,533 --> 00:30:07,077
You intend to make every choice for them?

399
00:30:08,954 --> 00:30:10,122
[sighs]

400
00:30:11,248 --> 00:30:12,499
"All people are equal."

401
00:30:13,583 --> 00:30:17,087
It is stipulated in our Constitution.
However, the existence of the Crown

402
00:30:17,170 --> 00:30:19,172
only serves to reinforce class divisions

403
00:30:19,256 --> 00:30:21,216
and undermine equality, does it not?

404
00:30:21,299 --> 00:30:22,342
Your Majesty, that is--

405
00:30:22,425 --> 00:30:24,094
Shielded by royal privileges,

406
00:30:25,470 --> 00:30:26,888
royal family members run amok,

407
00:30:28,807 --> 00:30:30,892
and the nobles aligned with them

408
00:30:30,976 --> 00:30:32,602
flaunt their power before the people.

409
00:30:33,395 --> 00:30:34,563
What do you think of this?

410
00:30:35,063 --> 00:30:37,023
[group murmuring]

411
00:30:39,067 --> 00:30:40,360
What you seek to preserve

412
00:30:41,695 --> 00:30:42,737
is neither this kingdom

413
00:30:44,656 --> 00:30:45,699
nor the monarchy.

414
00:30:46,950 --> 00:30:48,702
It is merely your precious noble status.

415
00:30:51,246 --> 00:30:52,747
[murmuring continues]

416
00:30:52,831 --> 00:30:54,833
[♪ tense music plays]

417
00:30:56,293 --> 00:30:57,294
Your Majesty.

418
00:30:58,336 --> 00:31:02,048
Having lived a life sheltered by privilege
in an unequal world, you may not be aware.

419
00:31:02,591 --> 00:31:05,385
But the Crown's contribution
to the nation is not just financial.

420
00:31:06,052 --> 00:31:07,929
Economy, diplomacy, and culture.

421
00:31:08,430 --> 00:31:09,723
-Its influence extends--
-[door opens]

422
00:31:09,806 --> 00:31:11,183
[Huiju] So?

423
00:31:14,227 --> 00:31:15,729
Is that why you tried to kill him?

424
00:31:15,812 --> 00:31:18,231
[♪ dramatic music playing]

425
00:31:19,065 --> 00:31:20,609
[murmuring]

426
00:31:23,820 --> 00:31:26,198
Economy, diplomacy, and culture.

427
00:31:27,115 --> 00:31:30,285
Did the threat of abolishing
such an influential monarchy

428
00:31:30,368 --> 00:31:32,329
compel you to attempt to assassinate…

429
00:31:35,999 --> 00:31:37,542
the King of this nation?

430
00:31:38,501 --> 00:31:39,502
Seong Huiju.

431
00:31:40,295 --> 00:31:42,297
[♪ tense music builds]

432
00:31:42,380 --> 00:31:43,506
Your Majesty.
STYLE
::cue()

433
00:31:52,307 --> 00:31:54,017
RECORDING 1

434
00:31:54,100 --> 00:31:57,812
[Jeongwoo] Do you wish to see your only
son follow in your father's footsteps…

435
00:31:58,313 --> 00:31:59,981
and be branded a criminal as well?

436
00:32:01,858 --> 00:32:03,526
[Yun] What is that supposed to mean?

437
00:32:04,027 --> 00:32:05,779
[Jeongwoo] I've only kept my mouth shut

438
00:32:05,862 --> 00:32:08,114
because I was worried
the Crown would crumble.

439
00:32:09,115 --> 00:32:11,284
[Yun] You worry that much about the Crown,

440
00:32:11,368 --> 00:32:13,411
yet you tried to kill I-AN?

441
00:32:14,871 --> 00:32:17,249
[Jeongwoo] I am willing to do
whatever it takes…

442
00:32:19,334 --> 00:32:21,002
as many times as necessary.

443
00:32:32,472 --> 00:32:34,140
The day I went to visit my father…

444
00:32:36,351 --> 00:32:37,769
[Jeongwoo] Let me escort you

445
00:32:39,437 --> 00:32:40,897
back to the palace.

446
00:32:40,981 --> 00:32:42,816
[phone buzzing]

447
00:32:42,899 --> 00:32:44,567
MY SON

448
00:32:50,782 --> 00:32:53,660
[Yun] This is what
Prime Minister Min had come to tell me.

449
00:32:59,708 --> 00:33:01,960
His Majesty cannot bring himself
to forsake mercy.

450
00:33:03,545 --> 00:33:05,588
However, you are different.

451
00:33:07,507 --> 00:33:09,092
When it comes to Prime Minister Min,

452
00:33:10,468 --> 00:33:11,803
no blow will cut deeper

453
00:33:12,804 --> 00:33:14,306
than one that comes from you.

454
00:33:15,098 --> 00:33:17,100
[breathing shakily]

455
00:33:27,610 --> 00:33:29,612
[group sighing, murmuring]

456
00:33:36,911 --> 00:33:37,912
Is this…

457
00:33:39,706 --> 00:33:40,832
all true?

458
00:33:46,296 --> 00:33:47,881
Answer me!

459
00:33:48,715 --> 00:33:51,384
Your Majesty, perhaps we should
verify the facts first--

460
00:33:51,468 --> 00:33:52,677
I asked the prime minister.

461
00:33:53,261 --> 00:33:55,722
-Please excuse the royal family--
-From now on,

462
00:33:57,182 --> 00:33:58,892
anyone who defends the prime minister…

463
00:34:00,894 --> 00:34:02,187
shall be deemed an accomplice

464
00:34:03,813 --> 00:34:05,315
to the one who sought my life.

465
00:34:05,815 --> 00:34:07,984
[♪ grave music playing]

466
00:34:09,778 --> 00:34:11,654
Your Majesty. [breathing shakily]

467
00:34:45,146 --> 00:34:46,147
Your Majesty.

468
00:34:47,023 --> 00:34:48,024
Go…

469
00:34:49,609 --> 00:34:51,069
and protect His Majesty.

470
00:34:51,694 --> 00:34:52,779
Yes, Your Majesty.
STYLE
::cue()

471
00:35:25,520 --> 00:35:26,521
Jeongwoo.

472
00:35:34,112 --> 00:35:35,238
Did you really…

473
00:35:38,658 --> 00:35:39,659
try to…

474
00:35:43,246 --> 00:35:44,497
Try to kill you?

475
00:35:51,504 --> 00:35:52,505
Yeah.

476
00:36:06,519 --> 00:36:07,520
Why?

477
00:36:15,653 --> 00:36:16,738
I begged you.

478
00:36:21,534 --> 00:36:23,203
I begged you to push Huiju away.

479
00:36:25,246 --> 00:36:27,165
I told you I'd protect you if you did.

480
00:36:28,666 --> 00:36:29,793
Time and time again.

481
00:36:35,840 --> 00:36:37,592
[breathes shakily]

482
00:36:58,613 --> 00:36:59,656
It's your fault…

483
00:37:02,450 --> 00:37:03,576
I turned out this way.

484
00:37:07,622 --> 00:37:09,624
[♪ gentle music playing]

485
00:37:12,794 --> 00:37:13,878
[sighs]

486
00:37:23,763 --> 00:37:25,223
It's your fault for thinking…

487
00:37:31,437 --> 00:37:33,273
I took her when she was never yours.

488
00:37:51,249 --> 00:37:52,292
[sighs]

489
00:38:39,005 --> 00:38:40,006
Are you okay?

490
00:38:42,842 --> 00:38:43,843
What about you?

491
00:38:57,273 --> 00:38:58,358
You did well.

492
00:39:00,735 --> 00:39:02,737
[♪ serene music playing]

493
00:39:12,372 --> 00:39:14,624
For the first time
in constitutional history,

494
00:39:14,707 --> 00:39:16,876
a nationwide referendum

495
00:39:16,960 --> 00:39:19,837
on the future of the monarchy
commenced at 8:00 a.m. today.

496
00:39:19,921 --> 00:39:22,340
This vote, which stands
to fundamentally reshape the relationship

497
00:39:22,423 --> 00:39:24,968
between the monarchy,
the government, and the people,
STYLE
::cue()

498
00:39:25,051 --> 00:39:29,180
is being widely regarded
as a defining moment for the nation.

499
00:39:29,263 --> 00:39:32,642
Following extensive negotiations,
the Crown and the government have agreed

500
00:39:32,725 --> 00:39:36,813
to put the question of abolishing
the monarchy to a public vote.

501
00:39:36,896 --> 00:39:38,648
Ultimately, His Majesty's principle

502
00:39:38,731 --> 00:39:42,610
that the people must decide
whether the monarchy is retained

503
00:39:42,694 --> 00:39:44,946
or abolished has prevailed.

504
00:39:45,029 --> 00:39:47,281
[♪ majestic music playing]

505
00:39:48,491 --> 00:39:49,867
What would you want to do first

506
00:39:51,119 --> 00:39:52,286
if it passes?

507
00:39:53,663 --> 00:39:54,789
Hmm.

508
00:39:56,666 --> 00:39:57,667
My name.

509
00:39:58,418 --> 00:39:59,419
Your name?

510
00:40:00,378 --> 00:40:01,379
Do you know my name?

511
00:40:02,171 --> 00:40:05,717
[chuckles] You think I don't know
my own husband's name?

512
00:40:06,342 --> 00:40:07,427
You've never used it.

513
00:40:07,927 --> 00:40:09,387
That's because royals…

514
00:40:09,929 --> 00:40:10,930
Exactly.

515
00:40:12,557 --> 00:40:13,558
So…

516
00:40:15,059 --> 00:40:17,812
if it passes, I want you to call me…

517
00:40:19,230 --> 00:40:20,231
by my name.

518
00:40:23,776 --> 00:40:24,777
I will.

519
00:40:47,842 --> 00:40:49,844
-[♪ sweet music playing]
-[Hyejeong sighs]

520
00:40:54,974 --> 00:40:56,142
It's the weekend.

521
00:40:58,478 --> 00:41:01,064
You should go
to the private residence and rest too.

522
00:41:02,148 --> 00:41:05,860
Well, I'm most at ease
at the palace. [chuckles]

523
00:41:11,491 --> 00:41:13,409
The thought of abolishing the monarchy

524
00:41:14,410 --> 00:41:15,953
must make you a little sad.

525
00:41:17,538 --> 00:41:18,539
Why?

526
00:41:21,834 --> 00:41:23,961
The palace is home to you.

527
00:41:24,045 --> 00:41:25,213
[laughs]

528
00:41:26,047 --> 00:41:29,383
Come on. Your family doesn't change
just because you move.

529
00:41:29,967 --> 00:41:33,805
I'll still have
His Majesty and Her Majesty.

530
00:41:36,933 --> 00:41:37,934
And you

531
00:41:39,143 --> 00:41:42,271
will be there as well.

532
00:41:43,189 --> 00:41:44,190
Right?

533
00:41:45,066 --> 00:41:48,277
[chuckles, clears throat]

534
00:41:48,361 --> 00:41:49,529
[chuckles]

535
00:41:53,366 --> 00:41:54,742
Hyeon, you have something here.

536
00:41:54,826 --> 00:41:56,035
Come closer.

537
00:41:57,078 --> 00:41:59,205
[♪ bright pop music playing]

538
00:42:01,040 --> 00:42:02,583
[giggles]

539
00:42:05,336 --> 00:42:07,171
Why? Am I moving too fast? Bad idea?

540
00:42:08,673 --> 00:42:10,675
[♪ romantic pop ballad playing]

541
00:42:11,926 --> 00:42:12,927
Good idea.

542
00:42:36,951 --> 00:42:39,036
Oh, my goodness.

543
00:42:41,414 --> 00:42:42,957
That's youth for you.

544
00:42:44,208 --> 00:42:45,751
My goodness.

545
00:42:47,753 --> 00:42:48,838
Let's go already!

546
00:43:01,184 --> 00:43:02,226
So cute.

547
00:43:09,942 --> 00:43:11,694
-[yelps, laughs]
-[giggles]

548
00:43:12,820 --> 00:43:14,280
That hurts.

549
00:43:15,072 --> 00:43:16,157
How about

550
00:43:16,949 --> 00:43:17,950
when spring comes,

551
00:43:19,076 --> 00:43:20,703
we go see the cherry blossoms?

552
00:43:22,997 --> 00:43:23,998
Sounds good.

553
00:43:26,292 --> 00:43:28,586
[both laughing]

554
00:43:29,754 --> 00:43:30,796
You're so short.

555
00:43:30,880 --> 00:43:33,841
When we go see the cherry blossoms,
I'm going to lift you up

556
00:43:33,925 --> 00:43:36,886
-and carry you around like this.
-[squeals, giggles]

557
00:43:36,969 --> 00:43:38,221
Just like this.

558
00:43:38,304 --> 00:43:39,722
[laughing]
STYLE
::cue()

559
00:43:44,310 --> 00:43:46,312
[♪ serious music playing]

560
00:43:53,486 --> 00:43:55,321
[I-AN] Thus proclaims the King.

561
00:43:55,404 --> 00:43:57,198
THUS PROCLAIMS THE KING

562
00:43:58,282 --> 00:43:59,575
For many years,

563
00:43:59,659 --> 00:44:02,495
this nation has maintained stability
through the Crown.

564
00:44:04,121 --> 00:44:06,499
At times, it offered protection.

565
00:44:07,833 --> 00:44:08,834
At others,

566
00:44:09,627 --> 00:44:11,337
it hindered progress.

567
00:44:13,673 --> 00:44:18,344
The people have spoken and have decided
to bear full responsibility themselves.

568
00:44:19,387 --> 00:44:20,721
In light of their decision,

569
00:44:21,222 --> 00:44:22,223
the Crown

570
00:44:24,141 --> 00:44:25,935
can no longer claim justification.

571
00:44:26,519 --> 00:44:29,146
-[♪ inspiring music playing]
-By the final authority

572
00:44:29,230 --> 00:44:31,107
vested in me by the Constitution,

573
00:44:32,275 --> 00:44:33,901
I hereby proclaim the abolition…

574
00:44:35,903 --> 00:44:36,904
of the monarchy.

575
00:44:39,991 --> 00:44:41,200
The 34th King,

576
00:44:42,368 --> 00:44:43,452
Lee Wan.

577
00:45:29,332 --> 00:45:30,708
[Wan] Huiju!

578
00:45:37,923 --> 00:45:38,924
Wan!

579
00:45:40,134 --> 00:45:42,345
[♪ uplifting pop song playing]

580
00:45:42,428 --> 00:45:43,554
Lee Wan!

581
00:45:44,055 --> 00:45:45,931
[laughs]

582
00:46:11,624 --> 00:46:12,833
-Let's go.
-Okay.

583
00:46:16,295 --> 00:46:18,297
[♪ song continuing]

584
00:46:36,357 --> 00:46:40,694
THREE YEARS LATER

585
00:46:43,072 --> 00:46:45,408
[♪ opening theme pop song playing]

586
00:46:51,539 --> 00:46:52,623
[reporter] Over here!

587
00:46:53,165 --> 00:46:56,127
[reporters clamoring]

588
00:46:58,421 --> 00:46:59,964
[news anchor] It has been three years

589
00:47:00,047 --> 00:47:01,841
since Ms. Seong
left her company for the palace.

590
00:47:01,924 --> 00:47:04,260
She has now returned
to the board to resume

591
00:47:04,343 --> 00:47:06,178
a frontline management role.

592
00:47:10,933 --> 00:47:12,643
Industry insiders believe

593
00:47:12,726 --> 00:47:16,647
her return will significantly impact
Castle Group's succession dynamics.

594
00:47:17,148 --> 00:47:18,441
As the nation's last queen

595
00:47:18,524 --> 00:47:21,235
and a leading figure
in the abolition of the monarchy,

596
00:47:21,318 --> 00:47:25,823
there is growing interest in what changes
she will bring to Castle Group.

597
00:47:25,906 --> 00:47:27,199
CASTLE BEAUTY CEO SEONG HUIJU

598
00:47:27,283 --> 00:47:28,701
How have you been?

599
00:47:29,577 --> 00:47:30,578
[sniffles]

600
00:47:32,163 --> 00:47:33,164
[sighs]

601
00:47:33,247 --> 00:47:34,415
I missed you so much.

602
00:47:35,040 --> 00:47:36,208
Are you really that happy?

603
00:47:36,750 --> 00:47:38,085
[Huiju sighs]

604
00:47:41,297 --> 00:47:42,298
-Move.
-[gasps]

605
00:47:43,257 --> 00:47:44,258
[sighs]
STYLE
::cue()

606
00:47:48,304 --> 00:47:49,305
[moans]

607
00:47:50,723 --> 00:47:52,391
It has been far too long.

608
00:47:53,893 --> 00:47:56,061
[sighs deeply]

609
00:47:56,687 --> 00:47:59,982
Let's just say you've been on sabbatical.

610
00:48:00,483 --> 00:48:02,860
Don't you think I work too hard
abolishing the monarchy

611
00:48:02,943 --> 00:48:04,069
for it to count as one?

612
00:48:06,822 --> 00:48:07,907
What? Hold on.

613
00:48:08,657 --> 00:48:09,658
What is all this?

614
00:48:10,159 --> 00:48:12,495
[Hyejeong] Senior Managing Director
Seong's projects.

615
00:48:12,578 --> 00:48:14,413
You asked me to organize
all related files.

616
00:48:14,497 --> 00:48:15,748
Why are there so many?

617
00:48:16,332 --> 00:48:17,875
He worked on a ton of projects.

618
00:48:22,087 --> 00:48:23,214
What in the world?

619
00:48:24,173 --> 00:48:25,257
[hisses]

620
00:48:25,758 --> 00:48:27,092
ADVERTISEMENT MODEL, SEONG TAEJU

621
00:48:27,176 --> 00:48:29,136
He made himself the face of the brand?

622
00:48:29,678 --> 00:48:32,806
-Who in their right mind would buy this?
-[knocks on door]

623
00:48:36,143 --> 00:48:37,937
-Hello, sir.
-Hi, Ms. Do.

624
00:48:38,687 --> 00:48:40,064
-Taeju.
-Yes?

625
00:48:40,147 --> 00:48:43,817
I'm currently reviewing
your project proposals, you see.

626
00:48:43,901 --> 00:48:46,070
-This is…
-No need to thank me.

627
00:48:46,153 --> 00:48:48,405
Can you just do me a favor?

628
00:48:48,489 --> 00:48:51,033
[scoffs] You're going to ask
for a favor too?

629
00:48:51,116 --> 00:48:53,786
I need you to manage Castle Card as well.

630
00:48:56,330 --> 00:48:57,331
What?

631
00:48:59,416 --> 00:49:02,002
Then, what will you be doing?

632
00:49:03,170 --> 00:49:04,964
Did Father ask you to go to Electronics?

633
00:49:05,047 --> 00:49:07,967
Don't kid yourself.
He's not retiring anytime soon.

634
00:49:09,301 --> 00:49:10,302
[Taeju clears throat]

635
00:49:10,803 --> 00:49:11,804
[Huiju] Then why?

636
00:49:13,639 --> 00:49:15,474
[laughs] How do I say this?

637
00:49:16,475 --> 00:49:17,476
Listen.

638
00:49:18,018 --> 00:49:19,395
My Dayeong is pregnant.

639
00:49:20,145 --> 00:49:21,605
[laughs]

640
00:49:21,689 --> 00:49:22,690
What?

641
00:49:23,399 --> 00:49:25,568
You're going to be an aunt, kid.

642
00:49:26,318 --> 00:49:28,404
-Congratulations.
-Thank you.

643
00:49:29,113 --> 00:49:30,114
So?

644
00:49:30,197 --> 00:49:32,575
What do you mean?
I need to go on paternity leave.

645
00:49:32,658 --> 00:49:34,577
She can't do all that by herself.

646
00:49:36,245 --> 00:49:38,497
[♪ tentative music playing]

647
00:49:39,248 --> 00:49:41,750
Have you lost your freaking mind?

648
00:49:41,834 --> 00:49:43,836
-Get back here!
-I'll take that as a yes!

649
00:49:43,919 --> 00:49:45,379
[Taeju] Thanks, I appreciate it!

650
00:49:46,630 --> 00:49:48,799
[Huiju sighs, groans]

651
00:49:48,882 --> 00:49:50,884
[♪ joyous music playing]

652
00:49:57,182 --> 00:49:58,809
You should just give up on cooking.

653
00:49:58,892 --> 00:50:00,477
Clearly, this isn't your strong suit.

654
00:50:00,561 --> 00:50:02,813
Hey, like you were so great
from the start?

655
00:50:03,397 --> 00:50:04,690
Yes, I was actually.

656
00:50:04,773 --> 00:50:05,774
Really?

657
00:50:10,446 --> 00:50:11,447
By the way,

658
00:50:12,740 --> 00:50:14,533
when are you planning to go back to work?

659
00:50:15,576 --> 00:50:16,660
[clears throat]

660
00:50:16,744 --> 00:50:19,913
I mean, you set up a whole foundation
after sorting out the royal assets.

661
00:50:19,997 --> 00:50:22,124
Are you just never going to
show up for work?

662
00:50:23,417 --> 00:50:24,710
I just need a little longer.

663
00:50:26,462 --> 00:50:28,047
I used to work day and night.

664
00:50:28,881 --> 00:50:30,424
I can take a bit more time off.

665
00:50:31,425 --> 00:50:33,552
I can review the key documents from home.

666
00:50:34,928 --> 00:50:35,971
But you know,

667
00:50:36,722 --> 00:50:39,308
most women aren't into guys
who don't have a job.

668
00:50:40,225 --> 00:50:41,810
-Really?
-Of course.

669
00:50:41,894 --> 00:50:44,355
I mean, look at how hard your wife
is working at her job.

670
00:50:44,438 --> 00:50:45,439
While you…

671
00:50:46,899 --> 00:50:49,818
If you just bum around the house all day,
it's not a good look.

672
00:50:50,361 --> 00:50:52,529
Hey, I'm not "bumming around."

673
00:50:52,613 --> 00:50:53,614
I'm resting.

674
00:50:53,697 --> 00:50:55,824
That's the same difference… sir.

675
00:50:56,700 --> 00:50:58,619
-Why, you…
-[phone buzzing]

676
00:50:58,702 --> 00:51:00,079
Unbelievable.

677
00:51:03,624 --> 00:51:04,625
Hey, Huiju.

678
00:51:05,250 --> 00:51:06,752
I'm cooking dinner.

679
00:51:08,045 --> 00:51:09,296
Are you on your way home?

680
00:51:10,172 --> 00:51:12,883
I don't think I can join you
for dinner today.

681
00:51:13,842 --> 00:51:15,886
Why not? Did something happen?

682
00:51:16,512 --> 00:51:18,180
No, it's nothing like that.

683
00:51:19,765 --> 00:51:21,558
I actually have another call coming in.

684
00:51:21,642 --> 00:51:23,936
Ms. Do won't be able to join you either.

685
00:51:24,019 --> 00:51:25,312
You two should eat without us.

686
00:51:25,396 --> 00:51:26,397
I have to go now.

687
00:51:26,980 --> 00:51:28,190
Wait. Hold on, babe.

688
00:51:28,273 --> 00:51:29,483
You're telling me this now?

689
00:51:29,566 --> 00:51:30,734
Hello? Babe?

690
00:51:32,277 --> 00:51:35,280
Why? Is she too busy for you? [laughs]

691
00:51:35,364 --> 00:51:37,282
Yeah. Ms. Do also can't make it.

692
00:51:37,825 --> 00:51:38,909
[shouts]

693
00:51:41,286 --> 00:51:42,955
I didn't see her yesterday either.

694
00:51:44,373 --> 00:51:45,374
I didn't either.

695
00:51:48,627 --> 00:51:49,962
[both shout]
STYLE
::cue()

696
00:51:52,423 --> 00:51:53,424
Hello there.

697
00:51:53,507 --> 00:51:55,426
I worked hard on that dinner.

698
00:51:55,509 --> 00:51:56,593
Why are we eating out?

699
00:51:57,177 --> 00:51:58,470
Wan, check your conscience.

700
00:51:58,554 --> 00:52:00,180
Who'd eat that? You want diabetes?

701
00:52:00,264 --> 00:52:02,224
-Why you little…
-Do you want to try that?

702
00:52:02,307 --> 00:52:03,392
-That one?
-Yeah.

703
00:52:07,646 --> 00:52:08,897
Mmm.

704
00:52:19,992 --> 00:52:21,285
What's with that face?

705
00:52:21,368 --> 00:52:22,369
What?

706
00:52:22,453 --> 00:52:24,663
It's nothing. I'm glad you're enjoying it.

707
00:52:24,747 --> 00:52:25,748
Is it tasty?

708
00:52:26,582 --> 00:52:27,624
It is.

709
00:52:27,708 --> 00:52:28,792
[laughs]

710
00:52:28,876 --> 00:52:30,002
Hold on a second.

711
00:52:30,753 --> 00:52:32,212
[Wan] That's new.

712
00:52:32,296 --> 00:52:34,047
It's nothing. Hyejeong kept saying

713
00:52:34,131 --> 00:52:36,759
she wanted this
to celebrate our third anniversary.

714
00:52:36,842 --> 00:52:38,260
You like it?

715
00:52:39,303 --> 00:52:40,429
It's not bad.

716
00:52:40,512 --> 00:52:43,098
-Wait, your third anniversary?
-Yeah.

717
00:52:44,558 --> 00:52:46,143
You guys should be hitting it soon.

718
00:52:46,226 --> 00:52:47,478
No, we're past that.

719
00:52:47,561 --> 00:52:48,604
When did you two start?

720
00:52:49,730 --> 00:52:50,939
Start?

721
00:52:51,023 --> 00:52:53,358
Come on. You know it was
all fake in the beginning.

722
00:52:53,442 --> 00:52:54,693
Watch it!

723
00:52:58,739 --> 00:53:00,032
It wasn't all fake.

724
00:53:00,115 --> 00:53:01,867
It wasn't all real, either.

725
00:53:06,705 --> 00:53:08,332
Maybe you can redo the proposal?

726
00:53:08,874 --> 00:53:09,875
Pro…

727
00:53:10,751 --> 00:53:12,544
-Proposal?
-Yeah.

728
00:53:12,628 --> 00:53:14,922
You don't even have
a wedding band. [exclaims]

729
00:53:20,761 --> 00:53:22,262
-Proposal…
-[phone buzzing]

730
00:53:24,556 --> 00:53:26,433
Hello, Court Lady Choi. I mean, Jinsook.

731
00:53:26,517 --> 00:53:27,518
I'm listening.

732
00:53:29,478 --> 00:53:30,479
Wait, where are you?

733
00:53:35,442 --> 00:53:36,527
[knocks on door]

734
00:53:36,610 --> 00:53:37,736
Come in.

735
00:53:44,034 --> 00:53:45,035
Father?

736
00:53:51,375 --> 00:53:52,918
I spoke with Taeju.

737
00:53:54,878 --> 00:53:56,129
Just prove yourself.

738
00:53:58,674 --> 00:54:00,801
I'll make sure the cards

739
00:54:01,552 --> 00:54:02,761
aren't stacked against you.

740
00:54:09,643 --> 00:54:11,186
[sighs, grunts]

741
00:54:11,270 --> 00:54:13,272
[♪ tender music playing]

742
00:54:23,448 --> 00:54:24,449
Huiju.

743
00:54:27,828 --> 00:54:29,788
I never wanted you to lose.

744
00:54:31,290 --> 00:54:33,876
I just wanted you
to stop fighting everyone.

745
00:54:39,840 --> 00:54:40,841
Now…

746
00:54:43,010 --> 00:54:44,386
I won't stop you.

747
00:55:08,660 --> 00:55:09,661
[chuckles]

748
00:55:16,418 --> 00:55:18,629
[exhales shakily]

749
00:55:22,591 --> 00:55:23,842
[Wan] Why would you

750
00:55:24,551 --> 00:55:25,636
gift us a bed?

751
00:55:25,719 --> 00:55:26,845
[chuckles]

752
00:55:27,471 --> 00:55:28,472
Just come.

753
00:55:29,556 --> 00:55:32,726
-Try sitting on it, Your Majesty.
-Stop calling me that already.

754
00:55:34,519 --> 00:55:35,520
[clears throat]
STYLE
::cue()

755
00:55:37,731 --> 00:55:38,732
Here we go.

756
00:55:41,234 --> 00:55:42,235
A bed…

757
00:55:43,570 --> 00:55:45,697
It's quite soft. [grunts]

758
00:55:49,201 --> 00:55:50,494
-Oh. Ooh.
-Ooh.

759
00:55:51,328 --> 00:55:54,164
-[chuckles]
-[laughs, sighs]

760
00:55:55,082 --> 00:55:56,500
Is it not comfortable?

761
00:55:57,000 --> 00:55:58,418
[sighs]

762
00:55:58,502 --> 00:55:59,586
It is.

763
00:55:59,670 --> 00:56:01,838
I hear it will help you sleep very well.

764
00:56:01,922 --> 00:56:03,382
He sleeps fine now.

765
00:56:05,050 --> 00:56:06,051
[clears throat]

766
00:56:06,635 --> 00:56:09,096
It has been over three years
since your marriage,

767
00:56:09,805 --> 00:56:11,848
but there is still no news of an heir.

768
00:56:11,932 --> 00:56:14,059
[coughing]

769
00:56:14,142 --> 00:56:17,688
I was hoping a precious bed
could lead to some precious news.

770
00:56:17,771 --> 00:56:19,439
-[clears throat]
-[laughs]

771
00:56:19,523 --> 00:56:20,565
Precious news.

772
00:56:20,649 --> 00:56:23,360
There will never be precious news.
They're both DINKs.

773
00:56:23,443 --> 00:56:25,487
-Choi Hyeon!
-DINK?

774
00:56:25,570 --> 00:56:28,865
Well, Huiju just started working again.

775
00:56:28,949 --> 00:56:29,950
And I…

776
00:56:30,033 --> 00:56:32,119
Is there something wrong with His Majesty?

777
00:56:32,202 --> 00:56:33,495
I said, I'm not a majesty!

778
00:56:34,746 --> 00:56:35,747
Follow me.

779
00:56:36,248 --> 00:56:38,083
No, wait… And also!

780
00:56:39,167 --> 00:56:40,502
I'm in tip-top shape!

781
00:56:55,016 --> 00:56:57,060
Oh, my gosh! [gasps]

782
00:56:57,936 --> 00:56:59,146
You scared me.

783
00:57:00,689 --> 00:57:02,065
Why aren't you sleeping?

784
00:57:02,149 --> 00:57:03,650
My wife wasn't home.

785
00:57:04,276 --> 00:57:06,737
How could I, as your husband, just sleep?

786
00:57:06,820 --> 00:57:07,988
[sighs]

787
00:57:08,947 --> 00:57:10,615
Sorry. You can go to bed now.

788
00:57:10,699 --> 00:57:11,742
Hold on.

789
00:57:14,286 --> 00:57:15,412
Did you need something?

790
00:57:16,621 --> 00:57:17,748
No, I…

791
00:57:19,958 --> 00:57:22,294
Seong Taeju told me
he's going to take some time off.

792
00:57:23,295 --> 00:57:24,671
I might be a bit busier now.

793
00:57:25,630 --> 00:57:26,631
All of a sudden? Why?

794
00:57:26,715 --> 00:57:28,467
He said Dayeong is pregnant.

795
00:57:29,301 --> 00:57:30,427
What?

796
00:57:30,510 --> 00:57:35,265
You know how professional executives
in this country are a dime a dozen?

797
00:57:35,348 --> 00:57:37,893
But he just had to…

798
00:57:37,976 --> 00:57:40,687
He just had to pick me

799
00:57:40,771 --> 00:57:42,939
and ask me to take over.

800
00:57:43,023 --> 00:57:45,692
Brother? More like a pain in the ass.

801
00:57:46,193 --> 00:57:47,319
[scoffs]

802
00:57:48,111 --> 00:57:49,112
You seem excited.

803
00:57:51,490 --> 00:57:55,118
Castle Card has
all the cash in Castle Group.

804
00:57:58,079 --> 00:57:59,080
I'm going to wash up.

805
00:58:06,046 --> 00:58:07,631
[sighs deeply]

806
00:58:24,189 --> 00:58:25,190
Should I get one?

807
00:58:26,525 --> 00:58:27,526
What?

808
00:58:29,653 --> 00:58:30,695
A ring.

809
00:58:31,947 --> 00:58:33,782
What ring?

810
00:58:34,616 --> 00:58:35,617
You know…

811
00:58:36,910 --> 00:58:38,370
Most husbands

812
00:58:39,120 --> 00:58:41,122
wear a wedding band.

813
00:58:41,748 --> 00:58:42,749
Well…

814
00:58:45,377 --> 00:58:46,628
Why bother?

815
00:58:46,711 --> 00:58:48,046
What?

816
00:58:51,883 --> 00:58:53,134
Why bother?

817
00:58:54,719 --> 00:58:55,887
[scoffs]

818
00:58:55,971 --> 00:58:56,972
Seong Huiju.

819
00:58:59,724 --> 00:59:00,725
Huiju.

820
00:59:03,103 --> 00:59:04,312
Babe.

821
00:59:04,396 --> 00:59:05,856
Ms. Seong. Ms. Junior Alum.

822
00:59:05,939 --> 00:59:07,482
-[snoring softly]
-Hello?

823
00:59:08,066 --> 00:59:09,067
Seong…

824
00:59:09,693 --> 00:59:12,070
[laughing]

825
00:59:12,737 --> 00:59:13,738
You're asleep.
STYLE
::cue()

826
00:59:24,916 --> 00:59:26,668
He was fussing over the cello last time.

827
00:59:27,460 --> 00:59:29,129
Now, it's the violin?

828
00:59:30,046 --> 00:59:32,507
He doesn't like the piano or the cello.

829
00:59:32,591 --> 00:59:34,092
Can't seem to find what he likes.

830
00:59:35,635 --> 00:59:36,887
Maybe he doesn't like music?

831
00:59:38,805 --> 00:59:41,641
My Yun will become a musician.

832
00:59:41,725 --> 00:59:42,893
Don't say such things.

833
00:59:42,976 --> 00:59:44,603
[chuckles]

834
00:59:44,686 --> 00:59:46,313
You know it's not that easy.

835
00:59:46,396 --> 00:59:47,564
[inhales sharply]

836
00:59:50,942 --> 00:59:52,360
Let me buy this one for him.

837
00:59:52,986 --> 00:59:54,905
Tell him it's a gift from his uncle.

838
00:59:56,031 --> 00:59:58,074
Then, please buy this one for him.

839
00:59:58,825 --> 01:00:00,619
-We'll take this one.
-This one?

840
01:00:02,245 --> 01:00:04,956
Hold on… How much is it?

841
01:00:05,040 --> 01:00:06,416
I'll ring it right up for you.

842
01:00:07,250 --> 01:00:08,835
Thanks. [chuckles]

843
01:00:10,503 --> 01:00:12,172
DREAM INSTRUMENTS

844
01:00:12,255 --> 01:00:14,674
We can have dinner together
when Yun gets out of school.

845
01:00:16,134 --> 01:00:18,136
No. He has to go to his math academy.

846
01:00:19,679 --> 01:00:21,306
He attends an academy too?

847
01:00:24,059 --> 01:00:26,227
Right, as he should.

848
01:00:27,729 --> 01:00:30,273
He should. He's almost out
of elementary school now.

849
01:00:40,617 --> 01:00:42,243
Get back safely, Wan.

850
01:00:43,203 --> 01:00:45,288
Thanks. You too, Irang.

851
01:01:05,058 --> 01:01:07,227
HYEON'S GARDEN

852
01:01:07,310 --> 01:01:11,189
[laughs] So, you're going to propose
to her again?

853
01:01:11,272 --> 01:01:13,984
You made a good point last time.

854
01:01:15,986 --> 01:01:17,278
I see.

855
01:01:17,362 --> 01:01:19,406
We could get new rings.

856
01:01:20,031 --> 01:01:21,783
A fresh proposal would be nice too.

857
01:01:21,866 --> 01:01:23,326
[coughing] Huiju. Behind you.

858
01:01:23,868 --> 01:01:24,869
What?

859
01:01:30,333 --> 01:01:31,334
[chuckles]

860
01:01:37,674 --> 01:01:39,718
[laughs]

861
01:01:40,969 --> 01:01:41,970
Did you hear that?

862
01:01:51,688 --> 01:01:54,691
Did you bring up the ring last night
because of the proposal?

863
01:01:55,859 --> 01:01:57,235
[laughs]

864
01:01:58,278 --> 01:02:00,405
I mean, you know. It was more like…

865
01:02:00,488 --> 01:02:04,492
For a second there,
I thought you were suddenly into jewelry.

866
01:02:06,619 --> 01:02:08,580
You don't want to wear a wedding dress?

867
01:02:09,956 --> 01:02:10,957
Why bother?

868
01:02:11,958 --> 01:02:12,959
[scoffs]

869
01:02:13,460 --> 01:02:14,461
You know,

870
01:02:15,045 --> 01:02:16,963
you've been saying that a lot recently.

871
01:02:17,047 --> 01:02:19,174
But to say "why bother" about our wedding?

872
01:02:19,257 --> 01:02:20,675
There's no room for "why bother"s!

873
01:02:21,301 --> 01:02:24,054
But we already did all that.
Why would we do it again?

874
01:02:24,137 --> 01:02:25,597
But back then we were…

875
01:02:25,680 --> 01:02:27,557
That's when I started
having real feelings.

876
01:02:28,600 --> 01:02:29,601
What?

877
01:02:33,063 --> 01:02:34,606
I guess it wasn't the same for you.

878
01:02:36,399 --> 01:02:37,776
[scoffs]

879
01:02:39,903 --> 01:02:40,904
Babe…

880
01:02:41,821 --> 01:02:43,531
Hold on. Babe.

881
01:02:46,367 --> 01:02:48,870
Wait, you're saying
that's when you started?

882
01:02:50,371 --> 01:02:51,748
That late?

883
01:02:52,832 --> 01:02:55,502
We kissed and stuff way before then.

884
01:02:55,585 --> 01:02:57,087
When did you start?

885
01:02:58,838 --> 01:03:00,048
What?

886
01:03:03,968 --> 01:03:06,471
[♪ ethereal music playing]

887
01:03:28,701 --> 01:03:30,870
When did you start
having real feelings for me?
STYLE
::cue()

888
01:03:36,543 --> 01:03:37,544
From the start.

889
01:03:39,838 --> 01:03:40,839
You didn't know?

890
01:03:42,632 --> 01:03:44,551
I started liking you way back when.

891
01:03:45,510 --> 01:03:46,511
Way back when?

892
01:03:47,470 --> 01:03:50,056
Exactly how long ago is way back when?

893
01:03:50,932 --> 01:03:53,810
When you first told me your name.

894
01:03:54,811 --> 01:03:55,937
[Wan] Who goes there?

895
01:03:59,274 --> 01:04:00,567
Your name.

896
01:04:01,651 --> 01:04:03,069
It is Seong Huiju.

897
01:04:05,905 --> 01:04:08,408
[Huiju scoffs] Back at that archery range?

898
01:04:09,200 --> 01:04:10,285
[chuckles]

899
01:04:11,452 --> 01:04:13,246
You were like a bright ember in the dark.

900
01:04:14,622 --> 01:04:15,790
I wanted to run after you.

901
01:04:17,750 --> 01:04:19,085
Since you were so popular,

902
01:04:20,086 --> 01:04:22,172
I kept hearing about you at school

903
01:04:23,214 --> 01:04:24,549
and even after graduation.

904
01:04:25,508 --> 01:04:28,011
I thought we'd run
into each other eventually,

905
01:04:29,554 --> 01:04:30,847
but it never happened.

906
01:04:31,514 --> 01:04:33,892
-Then, I saw you at…
-The Royal Birthday Banquet.

907
01:04:46,279 --> 01:04:48,656
[Wan] You were just as bright an ember
that day.

908
01:04:49,616 --> 01:04:51,910
[♪ ethereal pop song continues]

909
01:04:51,993 --> 01:04:52,994
So you ran after me?

910
01:05:09,219 --> 01:05:10,220
Yeah.

911
01:05:11,221 --> 01:05:13,973
As fast as I could
because I was afraid of losing you.

912
01:05:30,240 --> 01:05:32,492
THE CROWN'S FINAL DUTY

913
01:06:07,735 --> 01:06:09,362
[sighs]

914
01:06:29,257 --> 01:06:31,259
-[Wan] It was not mine when I wanted it.
-[whimpering]

915
01:06:33,136 --> 01:06:34,470
[Wan] It was mine…

916
01:06:36,514 --> 01:06:37,515
when I did not want it.

917
01:06:37,598 --> 01:06:38,599
[sighs]

918
01:06:40,435 --> 01:06:41,644
But in the end,

919
01:06:42,854 --> 01:06:44,105
it was my choice.

920
01:06:54,907 --> 01:06:55,908
[chuckles]

921
01:06:59,078 --> 01:07:00,079
I feel relieved.

922
01:07:04,125 --> 01:07:05,126
[chuckles]

923
01:07:05,710 --> 01:07:07,712
[♪ uplifting music playing]

924
01:07:17,388 --> 01:07:18,431
[Huiju] Babe!

925
01:07:20,850 --> 01:07:22,018
Sorry!

926
01:07:22,101 --> 01:07:25,104
[sighs] I'm sorry. Work took forever.

927
01:07:25,730 --> 01:07:28,608
Are you done with the exhibit?
We can look at it some more.

928
01:07:30,818 --> 01:07:32,028
No, it's fine.

929
01:07:33,780 --> 01:07:35,031
Let's go.

930
01:07:35,615 --> 01:07:36,866
Let's go.

931
01:07:48,628 --> 01:07:51,005
[♪ sporty rock song playing]
STYLE
::cue()

932
01:07:51,089 --> 01:07:53,674
[Hyeon] I'm going to eat this
in one bite. [laughs]

933
01:07:53,758 --> 01:07:55,301
Wan, over here!

934
01:07:56,636 --> 01:07:58,096
Hurry up.

935
01:07:58,179 --> 01:07:59,180
Ms. Seong!

936
01:08:00,473 --> 01:08:01,474
[Wan] Hmm.

937
01:08:03,226 --> 01:08:04,227
Let's wear them too.

938
01:08:05,144 --> 01:08:07,271
The jersey? You want to wear one?

939
01:08:07,855 --> 01:08:09,482
-Yeah. I like jerseys.
-[laughs]

940
01:08:12,110 --> 01:08:13,152
Let's go.

941
01:08:13,236 --> 01:08:14,779
-[Huiju] Hi!
-[Wan] Let's go.

942
01:08:14,862 --> 01:08:17,281
Huh? Okay, let's go.

943
01:08:18,449 --> 01:08:19,492
ALL SEATS SOLD OUT

944
01:08:19,575 --> 01:08:20,576
[crowd cheering]

945
01:08:20,660 --> 01:08:21,702
[Huiju] It's starting.

946
01:08:24,872 --> 01:08:26,124
-I have one too.
-Like this?

947
01:08:26,207 --> 01:08:27,291
[♪ upbeat pop song playing]

948
01:08:27,375 --> 01:08:30,169
-[all cheering]
-[crowd cheering]

949
01:08:31,504 --> 01:08:33,381
Castle Sharks! Yeah!

950
01:08:37,343 --> 01:08:38,386
Let's go!

951
01:08:38,469 --> 01:08:40,263
[crowd groans]

952
01:08:41,889 --> 01:08:43,266
Are you kidding me right now?

953
01:08:43,349 --> 01:08:44,809
You must be joking!

954
01:08:44,892 --> 01:08:47,562
Shark attack! Let's go, Castle Sharks!

955
01:08:47,645 --> 01:08:50,440
Shark attack! Let's go, Castle Sharks!

956
01:08:52,692 --> 01:08:54,735
[cheering]

957
01:08:58,531 --> 01:08:59,657
Why am I not getting any?

958
01:09:00,366 --> 01:09:02,535
-What the…
-What?

959
01:09:02,618 --> 01:09:04,454
That's us!

960
01:09:04,954 --> 01:09:06,539
Us? Let's do it.

961
01:09:09,584 --> 01:09:13,963
[crowd chanting] Kiss! Kiss! Kiss!

962
01:09:14,046 --> 01:09:16,382
-Kiss!
-Kiss!

963
01:09:16,966 --> 01:09:17,967
[Huiju] Sorry.

964
01:09:19,760 --> 01:09:20,928
Should we speed things up?

965
01:09:24,348 --> 01:09:26,017
We don't need to maintain decorum now?

966
01:09:26,601 --> 01:09:28,394
Yeah. No more decorum.

967
01:09:31,522 --> 01:09:34,192
[crowd cheering]

968
01:09:54,128 --> 01:09:58,382
[crowd chanting] One more time!
One more time!

969
01:09:59,634 --> 01:10:01,594
-One more time!
-One more time!

970
01:10:01,677 --> 01:10:02,678
[♪ pop song continues]

971
01:10:02,762 --> 01:10:05,681
PERFECT CROWN

972
01:11:50,995 --> 01:11:52,997
Translated by Justin S. Kim

973
01:11:53,080 --> 01:11:56,792
PERFECT CROWN
